    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Matthew",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 22,
        "summary": "Jesus gives the parable of the marriage of the king's son\u2014Pay tribute to C\u00e6sar and to God\u2014Worldly marriages endure in this life only\u2014The first commandment is to love the Lord\u2014Jesus asks, What think ye of Christ?",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And Jesus answered and spake unto them again by parables, and said,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The kingdom of heaven is like unto a certain king, which made a marriage for his son,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0gave a wedding celebration.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 5:34; Rev. 19:7 (7\u20139); 21:2; D&C 65:3.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And sent forth his servants to call them that were bidden to the wedding: and they would not come.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0they did not want to come.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Again, he sent forth other servants, saying, Tell them which are bidden, Behold, I have prepared my dinner: my oxen and my fatlings are killed, and all things are ready: come unto the marriage.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 122
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 135
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But they made light of it, and went their ways, one to his farm, another to his merchandise:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the remnant took his servants, and entreated them spitefully, and slew them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But when the king heard thereof, he was wroth: and he sent forth his armies, and destroyed those murderers, and burned up their city.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then saith he to his servants, The wedding is ready, but they which were bidden were not worthy.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Go ye therefore into the highways, and as many as ye shall find, bid to the marriage.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So those servants went out into the highways, and gathered together all as many as they found, both bad and good: and the wedding was furnished with guests.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 13:47 (47\u201353).",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1226
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when the king came in to see the guests, he saw there a man which had not on a wedding garment:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 19:8.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he saith unto him, Friend, how camest thou in hither not having a wedding garment? And he was speechless.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said the king to the servants, Bind him hand and foot, and take him away, and cast him into outer darkness; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 8:12 (11\u201312); D&C 77:8; 133:72 (71\u201373).",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For many are called, but few are chosen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:34 (34\u201340).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 22:14 \u2026 chosen; wherefore all do not have on the wedding garment.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then went the Pharisees, and took counsel how they might entangle him in his talk.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 12:13 (13\u201317); Luke 11:54; 20:20 (19\u201326).",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And they sent out unto him their disciples with the Herodians, saying, Master, we know that thou art true, and teachest the way of God in truth, neither carest thou for any man: for thou regardest not the person of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0you court no man's favor.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 152
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:23.",
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 196
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 173,
                        "end": 177
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Tell us therefore, What thinkest thou? Is it lawful to give tribute unto C\u00e6sar, or not?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 58:22 (20\u201323).",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But Jesus perceived their wickedness, and said, Why tempt ye me, ye hypocrites?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0are you testing. TG\u00a0Test.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Shew me the tribute money. And they brought unto him a penny.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he saith unto them, Whose is this image and superscription?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They say unto him, C\u00e6sar's. Then saith he unto them, Render therefore unto C\u00e6sar the things which are C\u00e6sar's; and unto God the things that are God's.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Citizenship.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Governments.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When they had heard these words, they marvelled, and left him, and went their way.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The same day came to him the Sadducees, which say that there is no resurrection, and asked him,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 16:12 (1, 6, 11\u201312); Acts 23:8.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Saying, Master, Moses said, If a man die, having no children, his brother shall marry his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 25:5; Mark 12:19.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ruth 3:13.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now there were with us seven brethren: and the first, when he had married a wife, deceased, and, having no issue, left his wife unto his brother:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Likewise the second also, and the third, unto the seventh.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And last of all the woman died also.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore in the resurrection whose wife shall she be of the seven? for they all had her.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus answered and said unto them, Ye do err, not knowing the scriptures, nor the power of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 138:1 (1\u20134). TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Teaching Mode of; Scriptures, Study of.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For in the resurrection they neither marry, nor are given in marriage, but are as the angels of God in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Resurrection.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Marry; Marriage, Temporal.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 131:4 (1\u20134); 132:16 (15\u201317).",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But as touching the resurrection of the dead, have ye not read that which was spoken unto you by God, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 32:9; 1\u00a0Ne. 19:10; D&C 136:21.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when the multitude heard this, they were astonished at his doctrine.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But when the Pharisees had heard that he had put the Sadducees to silence, they were gathered together.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then one of them, which was a lawyer, asked him a question, tempting him, and saying,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Test.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Master, which is the great commandment in the law?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus said unto him, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dedication; God, Love of; Love.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heart.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mind.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This is the first and great commandment.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commandments of God.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the second is like unto it, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 12:33 (13\u201337); Rom. 13:10 (8\u201310). TG\u00a0Law of Moses.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "While the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Saying, What think ye of Christ? whose son is he? They say unto him, The Son of David.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Davidic Descent of.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He saith unto them, How then doth David in spirit call him Lord, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If David then call him Lord, how is he his son?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And no man was able to answer him a word, neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0dared.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}